The second likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning) since the paper deals with the application of machine learning techniques to a specific problem. The third likely sub-category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) since the paper deals with the application of AI techniques to a specific problem. The fourth likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory) since the paper deals with the classification of signals, which is a problem in information theory. The fifth likely sub-category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) since the paper deals with the classification of radio signals, which is a problem in wireless communications and electromagnetic spectrum management, both of which are related to cryptography and security.
